HtmlBody:
Hi Kelly,

     Thanks for the dates/times, I will quickly poll our community to find the consensus and provide the dial-in info. Would you or your teammates have any issues if we recorded our session? We do so to ensure widest distro for folks that can't attend, so if anyone has druthers please let me know. 
 
     A few of the things I promised, below is a generic agenda for your consideration, by no means is it firm so please feel free to adjust as needed. And 2nd, attached is our EM-Dallas flyer for your consideration, we hope you or your team will be able to attend. 

     I'll send our community demographics in a follow-up email (sorry for spamming your inbox) so you have context for what the Elite Meet veteran community looks like as a run-up to the webinar. 

Draft agenda:
Pre webinar: read ahead / fact sheet (company to EM; EM to VF), VF bios, vet bios (if registered early)

Webinar (~1 hour total):
- Intros (name, job, location)
- (handoff to VF) VF orientation
- Culture
- Possible / historical veteran roles in VFC
- Application process
- Current priority fills / locations

Q&A (min 15min)
- sample jobs - senior/mid manager to executive - right fit (have example handy - fighter pilot +10yr/ SOF vet 10-15+yr)?
- What are your challenges hiring veterans? Or veterans fitting in?
- Right candidate profile? What do you look for in hiring at manager, senior manager, and executive positions

     If there's anything, please let me know. Thanks again for your support and patience! Hope you have a good Memorial Day weekend!

Cheers,

TextBody: Greetings,  Elite Meet has tons of professional supporters and hiring partners across the nation. In an effort to further streamline the networking and job position possibilities, we're allowing our Hiring Partners to enter the Elite Meet Private Group on LinkedIn. This will be a great place for you to connect with our members and post job opportunities to get immediate responses. Below is the link to request access. We ask that once you've joined the group to please introduce yourself with concise bullets of your background and what the members can ask you about. Our only asks is for you to stay engaged and be an active resource for our members to ensure your company and you get the results you're looking for. This page will be the quickest way to let you know about upcoming events in case your organization would like to participate.  Elite Meet Private Group on LinkedIn or copy paste the link below https://www.linkedin.com/groups/12180640/  As you may recall, we help Special Operation and Fighter Pilot veterans secure great careers with premier organizations. We do not charge veterans to join or employers to hire. Elite Meet is purely a 501(c)(3) non profit supported by donors and sponsors.  If you have any questions or need anything please do not hesitate to reach out.   Best Regards,  Henry D. Ages Director of Employer Relations | Elite Meet 334.447.0901 Henry@elitemeet.us
